# One Pan Cheesy Beef Taco Rice 

https://www.tiktok.com/@aussiefitness/video/7359533040030321941?lang=en

## (Macros: Per Serve - 4 Total)
524 Calories | 47gP

## Ingredients:
- 1 Diced Brown Onion
- 700g Extra Lean Ground Beef (959 Cal, 150gP)
    - 1.5 lb 10% lean ground beef (1088 Cal, 136 gp) (total: 555 Cal, 43gP)
- Taco Seasoning (Old El Paso Taco Seasoning - store bought or home made)
- 4 Diced Garlic Cloves
- 120g Tomato Paste (can be substituted for tomato puree, passata or canned tomatoes)
- 200g Washed Uncooked White Rice (approximately 600g cooked) (716 Cal, 13gP)
- 500ml Beef Stock (or just enough to cover the rice & beef) (15 Cal, 1.8gP)
- 100g Cheddar Cheese (404 Cal, 23gP)
Optional Toppings: Cilantro/Coriander & Light Sour Cream

## Instructions
- dice brown onion and sautee on medium heat until translucent, then add beef mince.
- Once nearly cooked, add 1/2 packet of Taco Seasoning and let it cook through
- Add diced garlic and mix
- Add tomato paste and mix
- Add washed uncooked rice and beef stock
- Mix and cover, simmer on LOW for 15 - 20 min, mixing every few minutes
- Sprinkle on cheese and cover for 5 more minutes

IMPORTANT NOTES:
When adding the beef stock you may need to use less/more depending on the size of your pan, add just enough to evenly cover the rice & mince.
While the mince & rice is cooking in the beef stock make sure to stir everything together every minute or so to ensure the bottom doesn’t burn.

